---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto py-8 px-4">
    <!-- Heading and Intro Text -->
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Species</h2>
    <p class="text-lg mb-8 text-gray-200">
      The characters in this journey 
    </p>
    
    <!-- Region Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      
      <!-- Region Card 1: Aeolian Archipelago -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/karkorte/kraken.png"
          alt="Kraken"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Kraken</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Krakens were former humans a long time ago from when the world started going underwater. 
            The effect of the power plant explosion has caused the area around the city to become radiated. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/mutated-humans/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Region Card 2: Lumea -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/karkorte/moby.png"
          alt="Moby"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Moby</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Mobys were former humans a long time ago from when the world first started going underwater. 
            The effect of the power plant explosion has caused the area around the city to become radiated. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/mutated-humans/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Region Card 3: Karkote -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/woodland.jpg"
          alt="Woodland"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Woodland Creatures</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            These creatures can be squirrels, chipmunks, bunnies, or any other small rodent-like animal. 
            The creatures, independent of what type of real-world animal they are based on, are biped creatures that have opposable thumbs and the ability to speak.

          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/woodland-creatures/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Region Card 4: Grønn Verden -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/sylvangrove/tree-person.png"
          alt="Ectopian"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Ectopian</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            The species that defected away from the AI-controlled dystopia - a group of humans whose biology have been effectively combined with plants as a result of their symbiosis with nature. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/ecotopians/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Region Card 5: Sylvangrove -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/aqualumean.png"
          alt="AquaLumean"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Aqualumean</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Featuring mermaid tails and gills on their upper body in which they can breathe underwater, they have innate physical abilities that allow them to travel rapidly and nimbly through the reefs and the currents
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/aqualumeans/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/aqualumean.png"
          alt="Atlantean"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Atlantean</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Humans found it necessary to move down into the ocean and create an energy powered ecotopia called Atlantis. 
            They were unable to live on land because of their own pollution. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/lumea-humans/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>


      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/parrot.jpg"
          alt="Atlantean"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Avenari</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            The Avenari are a relatively new species, native only to the Aeolian Archipelago. 
            When humans were forced to the tops of the mountains after the seas rose, they entered the domain of the birds. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/bird-pirates/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>